Mon, 22 Jun 2026 12:00:00 +0200  Santiago Silva <thayeeboi890@gmail.com>

* Release v0.1.0
    * Initial release of sehn, a simple minimal camera viewer for X11
    * V4L2 camera support with format negotiation (MJPEG, YUYV, NV12, H.264)
    * Photo capture to JPEG/PNG with configurable quality/compression
    * Video recording to MKV/MP4/AVI via FFmpeg (H.264 + AAC audio)
    * Burst mode with configurable frame count and interval
    * PulseAudio audio capture for video recording
    * X11 viewfinder window with XShm accelerated rendering
    * Right-hand panel with mode selector, shutter, and folder buttons
    * Right-click context menu with device/format/audio/control settings
    * Info overlay showing mode, resolution, framerate, and recording status
    * Flash animation on capture
    * TOML-based configuration (sehnrc.toml, themes.toml, keys.toml)
    * Customizable keybindings with modifier support (Ctrl, Shift, Alt, Super)
    * Theme system with dark/light variants and HiDPI DPI scaling
    * PTZ controls (pan, tilt, zoom) for supported cameras
    * Exposure, gain, white balance, and autofocus camera controls
    * EXIF metadata injection (optional, requires libexif)
    * V4L2 device, format, and control enumeration commands
    --list-devices, --list-formats, --list-controls
    * POSIX signal handling (SIGUSR1 capture, SIGUSR2 mode cycle, SIGHUP reload)
    * Borderless and fullscreen modes
    * Desktop entry with camera MIME type associations
    * SVG icon for freedesktop.org compatibility
    * Built-in default config creation on first run
    * Global and session capture counters
    * MIT license

